  773: bandwidth decays toward randomness as the world grows — a Condorcet
  774: (1785) aggregation logic, and we treat it as such: the jury theorem's
  775: known failure conditions (Austen-Smith and Banks 1996) define exactly
  776: the boundary the seventh experiment tests. Three
  777: qualifications carry the finding's honest weight. First, the same
  778: dispersed knowledge *without* an aggregation institution is wasted: the
