 1464: ## Appendix: E4 calibration targets
 1465: 
 1466: The E4-v4/v5 magnitudes are model-internal; the table names, for each parameter, the
 1467: real dataset that *could* inform it — making the boundary between model-internal and
 1468: empirically-anchored a visible line rather than a caveat buried in prose (details in
 1469: `research/e4-calibration-targets.md`). The central %-benchmark is an *output* the
 1470: model computes, but mapping it to observed realized-to-appraised ratios is **not a
 1471: direct overlay**: the two are different constructs (§6), so it is a **candidate
 1472: validation target requiring an explicit construct bridge**, not a one-step
 1473: calibration.
 1474: 
 1475: | Model quantity | Model value | Real-world proxy | Candidate dataset(s) | Status |
 1476: |---|---|---|---|---|
 1477: | central %-benchmark | 46–68% | realized ÷ appraised value | World Bank IEG ratings; Flyvbjerg megaproject DB | candidate target; needs an explicit construct mapping |
 1478: | η (harm-blindness) | 0–0.5 | passive vs active waste share | Bandiera-Prat-Valletti 2009 (83% passive, setting-specific: Italian standardized-goods procurement) | anchored-direction |
 1479: | β (voice inequality) | 0.2–0.5 | PB participation bias | NYC / Paris / Porto Alegre; Decidim / Consul | calibratable |
 1480: | q, m (detection) | q ≈ 0.5–1%, m in hundreds | complaint / whistleblowing rates | FTC Consumer Sentinel; NYC 311; Dyck et al. 2010 | calibratable |
 1481: | λ threshold | central ≈ 0.10 | procurement rents / bribe depth | Olken 2007; WB Enterprise Surveys | calibratable |
 1482: | penalty f | equal both sides | legal sanction scale | held equal (conservative) | scope choice |
 1483: 
 1484: The v1.14 four-scenario map (§6) makes the same anchoring explicit for its harm-myopia model: the visibility long
 1485: tail is source-motivated by heavy-tailed public procurement (Skuhrovec et al. 2013), participation by
 1486: participatory-budgeting turnout, and the harm-detection gate by the agenda-setting/salience literature; the
 1487: per-knob anchors and their strength are recorded in `research/e4-plausible-anchors.md`, with the reproducible
 1488: scenarios, frontier, and theorem in `scripts/simulation/e4-v5/` and `research/e4-parity-theorem.md`.
