audits\2026-07-10-round2\multidimensional-evaluation.md:7:The Path-B correction is substantively real: the controlling contract limits the surviving quantitative claim to a small, conditional selection effect, and the deterministic gate reproduces the reported NO-GO. The current manuscript, however, has not completed that pivot: its abstract and conclusion still use retired or superseded apparatus outputs as headline evidence, including +43% delivery and +53–54% selection, although the contract says a delivery-inclusive effect is future work and “not claimed here.” Several fresh defects weaken rigor further: earlier experiments are still called pre-registered contrary to the controlling contract, the E4 parity discussion reverses the meaning of a 0.89 distributed/central ratio, and the prominent ~10× capture claim is largely generated by stipulated detection and acquisition-cost asymmetries. This is a potentially useful and unusually specified architecture paper, but the current v1.13 draft remains a **major-revisions working paper**, not yet a clean architecture-plus-mechanism contribution.
audits\2026-07-10-round2\multidimensional-evaluation.md:107:**Would I recommend publishing the working paper now, as an honest architecture+mechanism contribution? No.** First remove or demote the old apparatus magnitudes from the abstract and conclusion, reconcile all preregistration labels with the contract, correct the E4 ratio/parity errors, and import the contract's welfare/scope limits; after those bounded revisions, an honest architecture-plus-qualitative-mechanism working paper would be defensible.
audits\2026-07-10-round2\high-value-improvements.md:203:### 15. Add automated bilingual parity and archive separation
audits\2026-07-10-round2\errors-and-contradictions.md:13:### M1. The paper reverses the E4 parity boundary in prose and misreads a central win as a distributed win
audits\2026-07-10-round2\errors-and-contradictions.md:15:The abstract gives the correct analytical inequality, `β < 1 − η`, but then says the advantage falls to parity “where a fully accountable planner faces a platform that silences the harmed” (`drafts/paper.md:38-43`; Spanish mirror `drafts/paper.es.md:42-48`). Those words mean `η=1, β=1`; the stated equality is instead `β=1−η`, hence `β=0` when `η=1`. The recorded `(η=1,β=1)` cell is `0.50`, and the results define ratios below one as central wins (`research/e4-v4-symmetric-frontier-results.txt:6-14`).
audits\2026-07-10-round2\errors-and-contradictions.md:17:The later explanation repeats the sign error: it says measured parity lies “inside the distributed's side” and cites `(η=1,β=0) → 0.89×` (`drafts/paper.md:835-840`; Spanish `drafts/paper.es.md:906-912`). The analytical note makes the same claim (`research/e4-analytical-backbone.md:75-80`), although the engine defines advantage as distributed/central (`scripts/simulation/e4-v4-symmetric-frontier.mjs:21-22`) and the result file says `0.89<1` is a central win (`research/e4-v4-symmetric-frontier-results.txt:12-14`). This is a round-1 miss, not an EN/ES desynchronization.
audits\2026-07-10-round2\errors-and-contradictions.md:19:**Correct value/fix:** state theoretical, noise-free parity as `β=1−η`; remove the “accountable plus silenced” description. Qualify the closed-form law as a bias-only result. For the implemented full simulation, say that at `(1,0)` the central arm wins `D/C=0.89`; the current claim that distributed variance is lower is falsified by the reported cell and must be re-derived or removed.
audits\2026-07-10-round2\errors-and-contradictions.md:23:The paper says the E4 frontier ranges from parity to “~1.8× of a full-information oracle” (`drafts/paper.md:785-793`; Spanish mirror `drafts/paper.es.md:853-861`). The engine instead defines `Advantage = distributed / central` (`scripts/simulation/e4-v4-symmetric-frontier.mjs:21-22`), and the stored `1.82` is printed under that distributed/central definition (`research/e4-v4-symmetric-frontier-results.txt:1-14`). The benchmark-normalized table reports the distributed arm at at most about 71% and the central arm at at most about 80%, not 180% of the benchmark (`research/e4-v4-symmetric-frontier-results.txt:19-45`).
audits\2026-07-10-round2\errors-and-contradictions.md:25:**Correct value/fix:** write “a distributed/central ratio from rough parity to about 1.8×.” If benchmark-normalized levels are intended, report the actual `% benchmark` figures. Replace the residual “oracle” label with “full-information benchmark.”
