audits\2026-07-10-round4\codex-run.log:1094:docs\101_CORE_V0_MINIMAL_PUBLISHABLE_MODEL.md:859:- **Adoption selects.** The model addresses whether the architecture can be built and how its *selection* mechanism behaves under a symmetric, delivery-at-parity test — not whether any authority wants it, and not a calibrated real-world delivery multiplier (a total delivered-value effect would need a separately identified delivery model; see the estimand contract). Deployment configuration for an authority that has decided exists (prospective baselines, credit attribution, official protection, a symmetry clause: `docs/109`), but the architecture will plausibly be adopted first by relatively clean or newly arrived sponsors, in the places that need it least.
