audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v4-mechanical-embargo.md:20:Section F uses present-tense control language (“backed by,” “rejects,” “throws”) for unshipped machinery (`audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/DESIGN_SKETCH_v4.md:154-170`). There is no package command for it (`package.json:6-8`). Consequently there is no executable evidence that unknown fields, hidden constants, unused parameters, bad output fields, or embargoed renderings fail. The three test families are good behavioral requirements, but currently are prose only.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v4-novelty-alignment.md:27:V4 calls the atlas a present contribution even though the sketch specifies future engine/schema work and contains no atlas artifact (`DESIGN_SKETCH_v4.md:154-170,184-187`). The fixed-threshold covariance formula is a useful E4 regression benchmark, but the prior review already identified truncated-normal signal ranking as standard and Böttcher–Klingebiel as the closest budgeted noisy-selection neighbor (`critique-v3-novelty-positioning.md:33-43`). “Our narrow, not-yet-matched synthesis” also sounds like an exhaustive novelty finding although the search was expressly targeted, not systematic (`critique-v3-novelty-positioning.md:15-17`; `DESIGN_SKETCH_v4.md:188-194`).
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v4-novelty-alignment.md:39:V4 correctly limits the convenience app to existence/direction, not population magnitudes (`DESIGN_SKETCH_v4.md:175-181`). The foundation instead calls Surprisingly Popular an established instrument for **eliciting `w`** and the F↔G gap (`research/e4-value-estimation-foundation.md:74-78`). Recovering a categorical truth under that method does not by itself identify v4's planner-specific project projection coefficient or its target-population transport map.
