+# Codex critique — full-paper E4 coherence (Track 1 / B)
+
+## Verdict
+
+**NO — the full-paper E4 narrative is not yet publication-ready.**
+
+The v1.14 map itself remains coherent under the comparative-institutions robustness bar: the pre-registered `Δ = 0.025` NO-GO is the near-parity no-myopia anchor; the extension conditionally maps where each institution wins under declared harm-myopia scenarios; the central-favourable endpoint is retained; and Finding 4 remains a distinct E4-v4/v5 institutional-knowledge experiment. There is no double-counting or result-shopping. The coherence edits introduce no new multiplier notation or calibrated-impact claim, and the pre-existing 2.19×/2.22×/2.26× apparatus outputs remain locally labelled as conditional and uncalibrated.
+
+## Remaining contradictions
+
+1. `drafts/paper.md:125-127` and `drafts/paper.es.md:136-138` still give the old exhaustive, gate-only account of the load-bearing contribution and omit the v1.14 comparative map.
+
+   **Exact EN fix:** replace “The load-bearing contribution is the architecture and the mechanism *direction*, not the multiplier.” with “The load-bearing contribution is the architecture and the qualitative mechanism, whose comparative scope the v1.14 robustness map delimits across the no-myopia and harm-myopia regimes—not the multiplier.”
+
+   **Exact ES fix:** replace “La contribución que carga el peso es la arquitectura y la *dirección* del mecanismo, no el multiplicador.” with “La contribución que carga el peso es la arquitectura y el mecanismo cualitativo, cuyo alcance comparativo el mapa de robustez v1.14 delimita entre los regímenes sin miopía y con miopía al daño, no el multiplicador.”
+
+2. `drafts/paper.md:565-566` and `drafts/paper.es.md:618-619` repeat the same exhaustive architecture-plus-direction claim in the governing quantitative-status capsule, immediately before the paper presents the map as part of the surviving result.
+
+   **Exact EN fix:** replace those lines with “The load-bearing contributions are the architecture, the mechanism direction, and the v1.14 comparative robustness map across declared no-myopia and harm-myopia regimes—not a point multiplier or calibrated impact.”
+
+   **Exact ES fix:** replace those lines with “Las contribuciones que cargan el peso son la arquitectura, la dirección del mecanismo y el mapa de robustez comparativa v1.14 entre regímenes declarados sin miopía y con miopía al daño, no un multiplicador puntual ni impacto calibrado.”
+
+3. `drafts/paper.md:1420-1427` and `drafts/paper.es.md:1510-1518` are the strongest contradiction: the conclusion expressly defines what “the paper actually stands on” as the small gate plus architecture/mechanism direction, omitting the v1.14 map from the claimed result.
+
+   **Exact EN fix:** after the existing sentence reporting the gate result through “research-program rebuild gate),” replace the remainder through “of the mechanism.” with: “The v1.14 robustness map treats that result as the near-parity no-myopia anchor and maps where each institution wins across declared harm-myopia scenarios, including a central-favourable endpoint. We therefore retire the compound multiplier an earlier version reported and rest on the architecture, the qualitative mechanism, and this conditional comparative map; its magnitudes are declared reference and stress points, not calibrated impact.”
+
+   **Exact ES fix:** after the existing sentence reporting the gate result through “reconstrucción del programa de investigación),” replace the remainder through “*dirección* del mecanismo.” with: “El mapa de robustez v1.14 trata ese resultado como el ancla de casi paridad sin miopía y mapea dónde gana cada institución entre escenarios declarados de miopía al daño, incluido un endpoint favorable al central. Por lo tanto retiramos el multiplicador compuesto que reportó una versión anterior y nos apoyamos en la arquitectura, el mecanismo cualitativo y este mapa comparativo condicional; sus magnitudes son puntos de referencia y estrés declarados, no impacto calibrado.”
+
+## EN↔ES note
+
+The four coherence edits are substantively faithful: header (`paper.md:3` ↔ `paper.es.md:3`), findings row (`paper.md:519` ↔ `paper.es.md:569`), What-survives (1b) (`paper.md:1086-1100` ↔ `paper.es.md:1174-1189`), and appendix note (`paper.md:1484-1488` ↔ `paper.es.md:1576-1581`). Heading structure is **17/17**, counting the H1 title plus all H2/H3 headings, with matching levels and order.
